PLplot is a cross-platform software package for creating scientific plots 
whose (UTF-8) plot symbols and text are limited in practice only by what 
Unicode-aware system fonts are installed on a user's computer.

The PLplot core library can be used to create standard x-y plots, 
semi-log plots, log-log plots, contour plots, 3D surface plots, mesh plots, 
bar charts and pie charts. Multiple graphs (of the same or different sizes) 
may be placed on a single page, and multiple pages are allowed for those 
device formats that support them.

Plot gallery: http://plplot.sourceforge.net/examples.php

Documentation: http://plplot.sourceforge.net/docbook-manual/plplot-html-5.13.0/

Output file formats: PDF, PNG, SVG, Xfig and others

Interactive platforms: Windows, X11

==============================

This package provides a complete, but unofficial, .Net binding for PLplot.   

The native PLplot library (x64) for Windows are included in this package.
For Linux, PLplot must be installed on your system and libplplotd.so must
be in your LD_LIBRARY_PATH. On Debian and derivatives this can be achieved by 
installing the package libplplot12.

Usage information: 
Create a PLPlot.PLStream object and call its instance methods.

Examples are available at https://github.com/DeepMLNet/PLplotNet/tree/master/Samples

and allows you to edit different document formats in your .NET applications.

- Doc

- Dot

- Dotm
- Odt
- Ott
- Rtf
- FlatOpc
- Txt
- Html
- Mhtml
- WordML
- PDF (only export/saving)

The GroupDocs.Editor for .NET Library allows to get document html representation that can be loaded into any WYSiWYG html editor. Edited html representation can be saved back to source format via GroupDocs.Editor.

The product has the following key features:
- Native API, allowing all application functionality to be programmatically controlled
- Translate document to html DOM for each document type
- Translate edited html to source document format
- Storage agnostic

For more details on the library, please visit GroupDocs website at:
http://groupdocs.com/products/editor/net

Note: The library comes up with some limitations in the evaluation mode. In order to test full features of GroupDocs.Editor for .NET library, please request a free 30-day temporary license.

PLplot is a cross-platform software package for creating scientific plots 
whose (UTF-8) plot symbols and text are limited in practice only by what 
Unicode-aware system fonts are installed on a user's computer.

The PLplot core library can be used to create standard x-y plots, 
semi-log plots, log-log plots, contour plots, 3D surface plots, mesh plots, 
bar charts and pie charts. Multiple graphs (of the same or different sizes) 
may be placed on a single page, and multiple pages are allowed for those 
device formats that support them.

Plot gallery: http://plplot.sourceforge.net/examples.php

Documentation: http://plplot.sourceforge.net/docbook-manual/plplot-html-5.13.0/

Output file formats: PDF, PNG, SVG, Xfig and others

Interactive platforms: Windows, X11

==============================

This package provides a complete, but unofficial, .Net binding for PLplot.   

The native PLplot library (x64) for Windows are included in this package.
For Linux, PLplot must be installed on your system and libplplotd.so must
be in your LD_LIBRARY_PATH. On Debian and derivatives this can be achieved by 
installing the package libplplot12.

Usage information: 
Create a PLPlot.PLStream object and call its instance methods.

Examples are available at https://github.com/DeepMLNet/PLplotNet/tree/master/Samples
